4.  LGD  will  be  the  Executing  Agency,  and  the  joint  secretary  of  LGD  will  head  the 
secretariat to assist CULG; other members of the secretariat will be provided by LGD and LGED 
and the secretariat will be established at LGED. Individual consultants with expertise in urban 
policy,  planning,  law,  and  local  government  finance  will  be  recruited  to  conduct  required 
background studies and assist CULG in preparing policy recommendations.  

5.  LGED will provide a fully furnished office (minimum space of 100 square meters) with 
sufficient communications (two telephone lines). One vehicle will be hired under the technical 
assistance (TA) budget; and the Executing Agency will provide additional transport for the 
counterpart  staff.  Also  to  be  engaged  under  the  TA  will  be  two  research  assistants,  one 
translator, and two computer operators/word processors.  

6.  CULG will convene meetings at least six times during its 2-year tenure. The chairperson 
may call additional meetings. CULG, with the assistance of the secretariat, will hold dialogues 
(at  the  national,  regional,  and  local  levels)  with  political  leaders,  policy  makers,  and  local 
stakeholders as well as local aid community in the urban sector; review the recommendations of 
similar  commissions/committees;  review  relevant  documents,  acts,  ordinances;  and  mount 
studies on key issues of urban local governance.  

7.  The  consultants  will  be  selected  and  engaged  in  accordance  with  the  Asian 
Development Bank’s (ADB) Guidelines on the Use of Consultants and other arrangements on 
the selection and engagement of domestic consultants. Six domestic consultants and one 
international consultant will be recruited on an individual basis. The outline terms of reference of 
the consultants are provided in Section E of this Appendix.  

D.  Cost Estimates and Financing Arrangements 

8.  The total cost of the TA is estimated at $520,000 equivalent. The Government has 
requested  ADB  to  finance  $400,000  equivalent  covering  all  the  foreign  exchange  costs 
($85,000) and part of the local costs. ADB will finance $400,000 equivalent, on a grant basis, 
from  ADB’s  TA  funding  program.  The  proposed  government  contribution  of  $120,000 
